You should start a background service, like `WorkManager`, which you can make it `Periodic` (repeat every 15 minutes minimum sported time). It will run even if your cellphone restarts. WorkManager is pretty easy to be configured and used.

Example: 

    class MyBackgroundWorker extends Worker {
      public MyBackgroundWorker(Context context, WorkParameters workParameters){
         super(context, workParameters);
       }
    
      @Override
      Result doWork(){
        //make room request here
        //after selection is successful schedule your alarm manager notification here
      }
    }

Now, how to start it:

On the moment you need it:

    WorkManager.getInstance(myContext).enqueue(OneTimeWorkRequestBuilder&lt;UploadWorker&gt;()
            .build());

